results.longDescription: The adventures of captains Kirk, Picard, Sisko, and Janeway have captivated Star Trek fans for decades, but their roots have never been fully detailed. How did the Federation, Starfleet, and the wisdom that brought both peace and all of those technological marvels come into being? In the fall of 2001, viewers got their answer in the person of Captain Jonathan Archer and the new series Star Trek: Enterprise. Set in 2151 — over a century before Kirk's voyages in Star Trek lore — and only 150 years ahead of our own time, Enterprise set out to explore a whole new world of the unknown. Earth's people have only just perfected the Warp 5 engine and a whole deeper region of space beckons. But in spite of the Vulcans' misgivings, whose "aid" many see as condescending and cautious, the humans strive to realize their potential. Archer is chief among them, but when he is forced to launch his new ship with T'Pol, a Vulcan first officer, a bond of mutual respect slowly grows between them that bodes well for humanity's maturity. Allies and enemies await discovery, protocols are unheard of, and a mysterious Temporal Cold War has focused on Archer's destiny. Will the crew of the NX-01 Enterprise have the raw energy, honor and guts to pioneer the way?

results.longDescription: Jonathan Archer quickly assembles a crew to return the Klingon to his people using Earth's first Warp 5 starship, Enterprise. When the ship is attacked, the Klingon is abducted, and Archer's crew is drawn into an intrigue that spans both space and time.

results.longDescription: Discovering a ship floating immobile in space, Archer's crew investigates and finds the incapacitated alien crew being drained of a vital chemical. When further ships arrive, the Enterpise is accused of the chemical theft.

results.shortDescription: Landing on an unspoiled world, Archer allows an away team to spend the night on the planet.
results.longDescription: Landing on an unspoiled world, Archer allows an away team to spend the night on the planet. Sheltering from storms during the night, the officers seek refuge in nearby caves, where they begin to hallucinate dangerously.

results.longDescription: A cloaked and damaged Xyrillian ship is discovered draining plamsa from the Enterprise. Sent to help the Xyrillians, Trip Tucker flirts with one of the aliens, and is later shocked to find he has become pregnant.

results.shortDescription: Dispatched to investigate the fate of an Earth colony ship which disappeared 75 years earlier, the
results.longDescription: Dispatched to investigate the fate of an Earth colony ship which disappeared 75 years earlier, the Enterprise orbits Terra Nova. Discovering little on the planet except unusual radiation readings, Archer's away team are ambushed by local cave dwellers.

results.longDescription: Urged by T'Pol to show respect, Archer and Trip visit a Vulcan monastery where they discover a troop of Andorians: blue-skinned suspicious, militaristic aliens, who claim that the monastery is actually a high-tech listening post.

results.shortDescription: Reed and Travis are dispatched to mine a rare mineral from a large comet, while the Enterprise
results.longDescription: Reed and Travis are dispatched to mine a rare mineral from a large comet, while the Enterprise maintains frosty contact with a Vulcan vessel. When his officers on the comet are endangered, Archer reluctantly asks for help.

results.shortDescription: Encountering a new civilization, Archer discovers that other space-faring aliens have already
results.longDescription: Encountering a new civilization, Archer discovers that other space-faring aliens have already arrived on the planet. Blamed by a woman for a widespread sickness, Archer investigates, and discovers the off-worlders are stripping the planet's resources.

results.shortDescription: Responding to a distress signal from a freighter which has been attacked by Nausicaan pirates,
results.longDescription: Responding to a distress signal from a freighter which has been attacked by Nausicaan pirates, Archer finds the freighter's crew have Nausicaan prisoner whom they are torturing for information. The freighter's acting captain is unrepentant.

results.shortDescription: A pilgrim passenger's calculated act of "sabotage" saves the Enterprise from later destruction in a
results.longDescription: A pilgrim passenger's calculated act of "sabotage" saves the Enterprise from later destruction in a plasma storm, and leads one of Archer's crewmen to reveal he is from 900 years in the future.

results.shortDescription: While the Enterprise fends off attacks from an alien vessel that refuses to communicate, Hoshi tries
results.longDescription: While the Enterprise fends off attacks from an alien vessel that refuses to communicate, Hoshi tries to discover Malcolm Reed's favorite food in time for his birthday. She comes away learning more about the lieutenant than the crew ever finds out about its mystery encounter.

results.shortDescription: When the Valakians ask for help with a planet-wide plague, Phlox realizes that the problem is
results.longDescription: When the Valakians ask for help with a planet-wide plague, Phlox realizes that the problem is genetic: the species is doomed in 200 years unless the immunity of the Menk, a simbiotic people that peacefully share the planet, yields a clue. But Phlox's cure brings up the ethics of interfering in natural selection: the Valakians' extinction would allow the Menk to fulfill signs of further blossoming. A soul-searching Archer agrees with him: the Valakian species is prolonged but not cured, in order to avoid "taking sides."

results.shortDescription: Detecting a disabled Klingon ship in the atmosphere of a gas giant, Archer sends an away team to
results.longDescription: Detecting a disabled Klingon ship in the atmosphere of a gas giant, Archer sends an away team to assist and revive its crew as a goodwill gesture. But finding human help dishonorable, the Klingons' lack of cooperation instead leaves the team trapped on the doomed ship.

results.shortDescription: Blaming Archer for the Andorians' destruction of their P'Jem monastery after it was unmasked as a
results.longDescription: Blaming Archer for the Andorians' destruction of their P'Jem monastery after it was unmasked as a front for spying, the Vulcans insist on recalling T'Pol for reassignment. But the two planets' dispute embroils Archer and T'Pol on an away mission on Coridan, where they are rescued by unlikely allies and expose the factions at play.

results.shortDescription: Conducting targeting tests well away from the Enterprise, Trip and Reed find themselves marooned on
results.longDescription: Conducting targeting tests well away from the Enterprise, Trip and Reed find themselves marooned on board a shuttlepod with no way to reach safety before their air runs out.

results.shortDescription: The Enterprise encounters a vessel manned by Vulcans who explore their emotions: a practice frowned
results.longDescription: The Enterprise encounters a vessel manned by Vulcans who explore their emotions: a practice frowned upon by Vulcan society. Although reluctant to associate with them, T'Pol finds herself intrigued by their experiences.

results.shortDescription: On a planet which has broken free from its orbit, Archer's away team encounters an Eskan party
results.longDescription: On a planet which has broken free from its orbit, Archer's away team encounters an Eskan party hunting a wraith. Approached by a beautiful woman, Archer learns that the "wraith" is a shape-shifter who needs his help.

results.shortDescription: The Enterprise crew is knocked out by four Ferengi who begin to scavenge items from the ship. Once
results.longDescription: The Enterprise crew is knocked out by four Ferengi who begin to scavenge items from the ship. Once awake, Archer realizes that the way to regain control of the Enterprise is to play to the Ferengi's greed.

results.shortDescription: Intrigued by stories of a "haunted ship" that crashed years before, the Enterprise finds the site
results.longDescription: Intrigued by stories of a "haunted ship" that crashed years before, the Enterprise finds the site and the crew soon spot figures who do not register on the sensors. When a desiccated corpse is discovered, a strange tale unfolds.

results.shortDescription: Having trespassed in the Tandaran military zone, Archer and Travis are held in a prison where
results.longDescription: Having trespassed in the Tandaran military zone, Archer and Travis are held in a prison where civilian Suliban are routinely detained. Disgusted that the detainees include children, Archer organizes a jail break.

results.shortDescription: After a disastrous diplomatic meeting, the Enterprise is invaded by a strange web-like creature,
results.longDescription: After a disastrous diplomatic meeting, the Enterprise is invaded by a strange web-like creature, ensnares several crew members, T'Pol and Hoshi try to find a way to communicate with it.

results.shortDescription: Archer receives orders to transport the Vulcan Ambassador V'Lar from the planet Mazar, where her
results.longDescription: Archer receives orders to transport the Vulcan Ambassador V'Lar from the planet Mazar, where her integrity has been called into question. T'Pol has difficulty believing that her former role model may be acting dishonorably.

results.shortDescription: Having repaired a crippled ship, Archer and Trip are invited by its captain to dinner on his desert
results.longDescription: Having repaired a crippled ship, Archer and Trip are invited by its captain to dinner on his desert planet. When the host's camp is attacked, the two officers flee into the desert, where they struggle to survive.

results.shortDescription: Arriving at Risa, the crew draws lots to determine who can take shore leave. Archer, Hoshi, Trip and
results.longDescription: Arriving at Risa, the crew draws lots to determine who can take shore leave. Archer, Hoshi, Trip and Reed all find companions for the short stay and experience wildly different consequences!

results.shortDescription: When Reed's shuttlepod causes an explosion that kills all the colonists on a planet, Enterprise is
results.longDescription: When Reed's shuttlepod causes an explosion that kills all the colonists on a planet, Enterprise is ordered back to Earth, its mission over. However, an agent from the future returns to demonstrate that more sinister factors were involved.
